## 2. Vulnerability Detection

### What It Means

Vulnerability Detection identifies known weaknesses in operating systems and installed applications. The Wazuh agent collects software inventory and sends it to the manager, which correlates it against a vulnerability feed.

### Why It Matters for GRC

Supports risk identification, risk assessment, remediation planning, patch management evidence, and audit readiness.

### Framework Mapping

| Framework | How Vulnerability Detection Helps |
|---|---|
| SOC 2 | Supports risk mitigation and secure operations |
| HIPAA | Supports security management process |
| ISO 27001 | Supports technical vulnerability management |
| NIST | Supports risk assessment and vulnerability monitoring |
| GDPR | Supports security risk reduction |
| HITRUST-style readiness | Supports risk-based remediation |

### Manager-Side Configuration

```bash
sudo nano /var/ossec/etc/ossec.conf
```

```xml
<vulnerability-detection>
  <enabled>yes</enabled>
  <index-status>yes</index-status>
  <feed-update-interval>60m</feed-update-interval>
</vulnerability-detection>
```

| Setting | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `<enabled>yes</enabled>` | Enables Vulnerability Detection |
| `<index-status>yes</index-status>` | Allows vulnerability data to be indexed for dashboard visibility |
| `<feed-update-interval>60m</feed-update-interval>` | Updates the vulnerability feed every 60 minutes (the default/minimum) |

### Commands Used (Ubuntu Manager)

```bash
sudo systemctl restart wazuh-manager
```
Restarts the manager so config changes take effect.

```bash
sudo systemctl status wazuh-manager
```
Checks whether the manager service is running.

### Commands Used (macOS Agent Version Checks)

```bash
/Applications/Google\ Chrome.app/Contents/MacOS/Google\ Chrome --version
```
Checks installed Chrome version.

```bash
/Applications/Wireshark.app/Contents/MacOS/Wireshark --version
```
Checks installed Wireshark version.

```bash
python3 -m pip show setuptools
```
Shows the installed `setuptools` package version.

```bash
python3 -m pip install --upgrade setuptools
```
Upgrades the Python `setuptools` package.

### Example Findings From Lab

Wazuh identified High severity vulnerabilities affecting Chrome, Adobe Acrobat, Wireshark, and `setuptools`.

### GRC Evidence Statement

Wazuh Vulnerability Detection identified vulnerable applications on the macOS endpoint. Findings were reviewed, prioritized, patched, and validated — supporting vulnerability management, risk assessment, and remediation tracking.

