## 5. Security Alerts

### What They Mean

Alerts are notifications generated when Wazuh processes events and matches them against rules.

### Alert Storage Location (Ubuntu Manager)

```text
/var/ossec/logs/alerts/alerts.json
/var/ossec/logs/alerts/alerts.log
```

### Alert Threshold

```bash
sudo nano /var/ossec/etc/ossec.conf
```

```xml
<alerts>
  <log_alert_level>3</log_alert_level>
  <email_alert_level>12</email_alert_level>
</alerts>
```

| Setting | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `<log_alert_level>3</log_alert_level>` | Alerts level 3 or higher are stored by default |
| `<email_alert_level>12</email_alert_level>` | Email alerts trigger only for higher-severity events |

### Commands Used to Read Alerts

```bash
sudo tail -n 20 /var/ossec/logs/alerts/alerts.json
```
Shows the last 20 JSON alerts.

```bash
sudo tail -f /var/ossec/logs/alerts/alerts.json
```
Watches new alerts live as they come in.

```bash
sudo grep -i "rootcheck" /var/ossec/logs/alerts/alerts.json | tail -n 10
```
Searches for rootcheck alerts.

```bash
sudo grep -i "55555" /var/ossec/logs/alerts/alerts.json | wc -l
```
Counts how many alerts mention port 55555.

```bash
sudo grep -i "55555" /var/ossec/logs/alerts/alerts.json | jq '{timestamp: .timestamp, agent: .agent.name, agent_ip: .agent.ip, rule_id: .rule.id, rule_level: .rule.level, rule_description: .rule.description, decoder: .decoder.name, location: .location, full_log: .full_log}'
```
Extracts important, readable fields from the matching alert.

### How to Read a Wazuh Alert

| Field | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `timestamp` | When the event happened |
| `agent.name` | Which endpoint reported it |
| `agent.ip` | IP address of the endpoint |
| `rule.id` | Wazuh rule that triggered |
| `rule.level` | Severity level |
| `rule.description` | What Wazuh thinks happened |
| `decoder.name` | Parser used to understand the log |
| `location` | Where the event came from |
| `full_log` | Raw alert message |

### SOC Analyst Alert Formula

```text
WHO + WHAT + WHERE + WHEN + SEVERITY + IMPACT + ACTION
```

**Example:**
```text
WHO: Lafleur.local
WHAT: Rootcheck detected hidden port 55555
WHERE: macOS endpoint
WHEN: 2026-07-12
SEVERITY: Rule level 7
IMPACT: Possible hidden service or rootkit behavior
ACTION: Investigate open ports, running services, and validate whether false positive
```

