## 9. Rootcheck Scan Timing

### Default Behavior

Rootcheck scans run every 12 hours by default; frequency can be customized.

### macOS Agent Rootcheck Configuration

```xml
<rootcheck>
  <disabled>no</disabled>
  <check_files>yes</check_files>
  <check_trojans>yes</check_trojans>
  <check_dev>yes</check_dev>
  <check_sys>yes</check_sys>
  <check_pids>yes</check_pids>
  <check_ports>yes</check_ports>
  <check_if>yes</check_if>
  <frequency>86400</frequency>
  <skip_nfs>yes</skip_nfs>
</rootcheck>
```

| Setting | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `<disabled>no</disabled>` | Rootcheck is enabled |
| `<check_ports>yes</check_ports>` | Checks for hidden ports |
| `<frequency>86400</frequency>` | Scans every 24 hours |
| `<frequency>60</frequency>` | Scans every 60 seconds — for short testing only, not permanent use |

### Temporary Testing Workflow

1. Change frequency to 60 seconds.
2. Restart Wazuh agent.
3. Wait for test scan.
4. Review alerts.
5. Change frequency back to 86400.
6. Restart Wazuh agent again.

```bash
sudo nano /Library/Ossec/etc/ossec.conf
sudo /Library/Ossec/bin/wazuh-control restart
sudo /Library/Ossec/bin/wazuh-control status
```

